The paper discusses a defense against a traffic analysis attack, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The defense is based on deep learning, which suggests the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attack and defense both involve analyzing network traffic, which suggests the paper may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique for generating traces, which may also place it under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
